s of unstructured responses for the user researcher to sift through and man=
ually tag and categorize, followed by a presentation to the exec or product=
 team, from which a decision may or may not be made, three months after the=
 question was asked.</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-h=
eight: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">That process makes sense for big, irrevers=
ible projects like rebrands, market expansions, and&nbsp; product extension=
s, but it&#8217;s far too slow for most of the things for which a tech comp=
any needs user insights. So companies often just skip structured customer r=
esearch, and rely on numbers and anecdotes to make product decisions. That&=
#8217;s a problem: companies have modern tools like Amplitude and Segment t=
o tell them <em>what</em> is happening in their product, but only slow, out=
